# Licensing for TheCommons

## 1. Documentation & Manifesto
All text, project ideas, and governance frameworks in this repository are licensed under the **Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC-BY-SA 4.0)**.

**You are free to:**
* **Share:** Copy and redistribute the material in any medium or format.
* **Adapt:** Remix, transform, and build upon the material for any purpose, even commercially.

**Under the following terms:**
* **Attribution:** You must give appropriate credit to "TheCommons (github.com/rvishravars/thecommons)" and provide a link to the license.
* **ShareAlike:** If you remix, transform, or build upon the material, you must distribute your contributions under the same license as the original.

## 2. Software & AI Logic
All source code (The AI Scribe, automated scripts, and platform architecture) is licensed under the **GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL-3.0)**. 

This ensures that any "Software-as-a-Service" built using this logic must also contribute its source code back to the community.